rComments: One of my favourite courses taken in my undergraduate! Vance explains concepts well and in an interesting matter. He's a great professor who really cares about his students and wants them to succeed. You definitely need to review and understand the material, not just memorize it. Would 100% recommend this course with Vance.

Dr. Trudeau is an amazing professor. He truly cares that you UNDERSTAND the material, rather than memorizing and regurgitating information. As a graduate course, the workload was heavy. Dr. Trudeau was always available to answer questions outside of class and was quick to reply to emails. He always provides great feedback. I recommend him highly!

A very good professor! Very kind,caring and will answer your questions in person outside class to make you get good grades that you want. His lectures are very very interesting and he makes learning the content a breeze! The material actually seems to be easy, although its a fourth year class. Definitely recommended prof and teacher!

This is an amazing 4th year endocrinology professor. his lectures are crystal clear, and he is super passionate about it all. Office hours are extremely useful and he is so encouraging and knows how to motivate you. Fun and informative class. The exams are essay style, so needs memorization and understanding. But it is fun stuff!

Best course I took in my whole undergraduate degree. Class size was small, extremely interactive. Vance is passionate about what he does, his lectures are far from dry. Exams are short/long answer questions which I loved, as opposed to standard MCQ. Gives you a chance to show your knowledge. Would highly recommend this class to any biology student!

He's a good prof but you need to work hard to get the grades. Exams are short-long answer questions that focus on the comparative aspect of the course. So you need to explain differences between species. I was intimidated at first with all the concepts but it's super interesting. Group project is graded in part by the students and so boosts grade

Fourth year course so it's expected to be challenging and difficult. If you're in physiology take it hopefully you don't have Trudeau, quite disorganized and favours students that are or will be working in his labs, prepare yourself for "mandatory" readings from text, lots of journals and presentations. Midterm/final write fast!

Excellent endocrinology course. This guy knows his stuff and if you work hard throughout the course you will do well. Vance is very helpful and an exceptional lecturer. His booming radio voice is awesome. Beware, that if you aren't interested in hormones THEN THIS COURSE IS NOT FOR YOU.
